    <header>
        <h1>About Git</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>What is Git?</h2>
            <p>Git is a distributed version control system that allows multiple developers to work on a project simultaneously. It helps track changes in the codebase and enables easy collaboration and code management.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Key Features of Git</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Version control: Tracks and manages changes to files.</li>
                <li>Branching and merging: Allows experimentation without affecting the main project.</li>
                <li>Distributed: Every developer has a full copy of the repository.</li>
                <li>Collaboration: Enables multiple contributors to work on different parts of a project.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Common Use Cases</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Managing source code in software development projects.</li>
                <li>Collaborating with other developers on open-source projects.</li>
                <li>Tracking changes in websites, documentation, and other projects.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>

